commentTextItems.html: appeal for lbw but turned down

commentPostTextItems.html: Umpires call on the ground staff to bring on the covers
More covers aclled on and it`s raining much harder now
The rain as stopped and the covers are been removed so the umpires can take a look
The covers are called back on due to more rain
18.03 Local time (16.03 GMT), The rain as stopped once again and news from the umpires is that play will start 18:30 pm local time, 16.30 GMT and overs have been reduced to 38 overs
18.20 Local time (16.20 GMT), Once again some sad news, it`s raining again and covers called back on, will advise what happens from here on
At this stage it looks like the rain is going to be the winner off this Afro-Asia Cup
18.31 local time (16.31 GMT), Sorry to say but the rain as won the today. The game has been called off

milestones.description: Prince has broken the record for most ducks (2) in ODIs for AFR, going past Justin Ontong's 1
Shaun Pollock has become the top wicket-taker for AFR in ODIs with 4 wickets, going past Kallis's 3
Heath Streak and Shaun Pollock's 51-run partnership is AFR's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 12 between Nicky Boje and Prince
Abdul Razzaq has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for ASIA, going past Zaheer Khan
Shaun Pollock has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3) for AFR, going past Nicky Boje
